RT  Isolation of human NURF: a regulator of Engrailed gene 
RT  expression. 
RA  Barak O; Lazzaro MA; Lane WS; Speicher DW; Picketts DJ; 
RA  Shiekhattar R; 
RL  EMBO J. 2003;22:6089-6100.
CC  The NURF (nucleosome remodeling factor) complex 
CC  catalyzes ATP-dependent nucleosome sliding and 
CC  facilitates transcription of chromatin [1]. It 
CC  recognizes H3 tails trimethylated on 'Lys-4' 
CC  (H3K4me3), which mark transcription start sites of 
CC  virtually all active genes [2]. In Drosophila
CC  melanogaster, the complex is composed of Caf1, 
CC  E(bx), Nurf-38 and Iswi [3]. In human the complex
CC  consists of SMARCA1; BPTF; RBBP4 and RBBP7 [4].
